Sentencas: In order to develop a simple and cost-effective route to fabricate proton-conductor intermediate-temperature SOFCs, a dense BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY) electrolyte was fabricated on a porous anode by in situ drop-coating.
Titulo: In situ drop-coated BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based proton-conductor solid oxide fuel cells with a novel layered PrBaCuFeO5+δ cathode

Sentencas: The PrBaCuFeO5+delta (PBCF) composite oxide with layered perovskite structure was synthesized by auto ignition process and examined as a novel cathode for proton-conductor IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: In situ drop-coated BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based proton-conductor solid oxide fuel cells with a novel layered PrBaCuFeO5+δ cathode

Sentencas: The single cell, consisting of PBCF/BZCY/NiO-BZCY structure, was assembled and tested from 600 to 700 degrees C with humidified hydrogen (similar to 3% H2O) as the fuel and the static air as the oxidant.
Titulo: In situ drop-coated BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based proton-conductor solid oxide fuel cells with a novel layered PrBaCuFeO5+δ cathode

Sentencas: An open-circuit potential of 1.01 V and a maximum power density of 445 mWcm(-2) at 700 degrees C were obtained for the single cell.
Titulo: In situ drop-coated BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based proton-conductor solid oxide fuel cells with a novel layered PrBaCuFeO5+δ cathode

Sentencas: A relatively low interfacial polarization resistance of 0.15 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C indicated that the PBCF is a promising cathode for proton-conductor IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: In situ drop-coated BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based proton-conductor solid oxide fuel cells with a novel layered PrBaCuFeO5+δ cathode
